review_text:
>Become Leon Kennedy;
>Invade the Spanish village;
>Shout at its inhabitants in a language they do not understand;
>Insult their cooking;
>When the villagers try to defend themselves, kick them in the head, breaking their necks;
>"I think there's something wrong with these villagers.";
>Continue the massacre of the entire village.

Pros:
1. Optimisation is kinda good;
2. Gunplay is ok, but not great;
3. Animations is ok;
4. Graphics are fine overall.
Cons:
1. Some locations are unbalanced asf on the 'Hardcore' difficulty.
2. Most of the textures (MAX settings) actually look like a 2015 game.
3. Becomes a bit boring starting from Chapter 14 I think.

The main story actually came out less interesting than the 'Separate Ways' DLC (because of the momentum and bossfights in the DLC). 
72 / 100 for me (with DLC);
65 / 100 Main story.
